"Out of the night that covers me,
Black as the pit from pole to pole,
I thank whatever gods may be
For my unconquerable soul.

In the fell clutch of circumstance
I have not winced nor cried aloud.
Under the bludgeonings of chance
My head is bloody, but unbowed.

Beyond this place of wrath and tears
Looms but the Horror of the shade,
And yet the menace of the years
Finds and shall find me unafraid.

It matters not how strait the gate,
How charged with punishments the scroll,
I am the master of my fate,
I am the captain of my soul.”

Monkey #2348 was minding his own business when the panel from a decaying satellite re-entered earth's atmosphere, burned up up re-entry, and the tiniest shard of its surviving form plunged directly into the monkey's drink. The monkey drank this shard along with his eggnog about a week ago. The shard punctured the monkey's intestines, but the monkey didn't think much of it until sepsis set in last night. After a long day of crawling in unimaginable pain towards the nearest land-line phone in his home (he used up his cell's battery playing games and didn't think to plug it in) he finally expired this evening about a foot short of his goal.

Monkey 2346 was driving home late at night when he hit a deer. He didn't die, but the deer did, and his car was wrecked. He decided to cook the deer, but he didn't know how, so he ended up cutting himself with his pocket knife while trying to remove the deer skin. It wasn't too bad, and he could hear the sound of water rushing nearby, so he went there to wash his wound. The water was dirty though, and the wound got infected, and Mr. Monkey got a fever. The next day he was so tired he rested under a tree. He didn't realize though that the tree was old and rotten and a branch fell on his head. He got knocked out instantly, and while laying on the ground unconscious a wolf came and tried to eat him. A random hunter shot the wolf, fortunately, and he rescued Mr. Monkey and tended to his wounds. The hunter bid farewell and the monkey walked home, only to be shot by the hunter because he stole his money.

by Baloo Kingdom » Mon Jan 04, 2021 7:12 am

The fate of Monkey 2345:

The Anti Monkey looked at the spiky baseball bat in his hands and felt sad. He walked over to the window and reflected on his boo surroundings. He had always hated spooky the spooky jungle with its terrible, tame trees. It was a place that encouraged his tendency to feel sad. Then he saw something in the distance, or rather someone. It was the figure of Monkey 2345. Monkey was a hungry monster with wobbly arms and dirty hair. The Anti Monkey gulped. He glanced at his own reflection. He was a snooty, cowardly, questionable coffee drinker with skinny arms and vast hair. His friends saw him as a soft, scandalous slime. Once, he had even brought a hot injured bird back from the brink of death. But not even a snooty person who had once brought a hot injured bird back from the brink of death, was prepared for what Monkey had in store today. The rain hammered like running dog, making The Anti Monkey mad. As The Anti Monkey stepped outside and Monkey came closer, he could see the sweet glint in his eye. "I am here because I want revenge," Monkey bellowed, in an energetic tone. He slammed his fist against The Anti Monkey's chest, with the force of 2178 quagga. "I frigging hate you, The Anti Monkey ." The Anti Monkey looked back, even more mad and still holding the spiky baseball bat. "Monkey, go away," he replied. They looked at each other with upset feelings, like two colossal, cold cat attacking at a very clumsy Monkey Day, which had jazz music playing in the background and two scheming uncles chasing to the beat. Suddenly, Monkey lunged forward and tried to punch The Anti Monkey in the face. Quickly, The Anti Monkey grabbed the spiky baseball bat and brought it down on Monkey's skull. Monkey's wobbly arms trembled and his dirty hair wobbled. He looked unsettled, his body raw like a mammoth, muddy mace. Then he let out an agonising groan and collapsed onto the ground. Moments later Monkey 2345 was dead. The Anti Monkey went back inside and made himself a nice drink of questionable coffee.

(This scenario was randomly generated)
